[Unknown]: question? I'm so sorry. I don't even know what I set out to answer.

00:41:04.560 --> 00:41:09.680
[Unknown]: That's okay. So, my question was, is there room for more political thought?

00:41:11.360 --> 00:41:15.600
[Amit Varma]: It's an unknown unknown, right? It's an unknown unknown, so I wouldn't know it. I can engage with

00:41:15.600 --> 00:41:20.000
[Amit Varma]: all of these frameworks of thinking, like Arnold Kling wrote a great book called The Three Languages

00:41:20.000 --> 00:41:26.800
[Amit Varma]: of Politics, where he says that left liberals, libertarians and conservatives frequently talk past

00:41:26.800 --> 00:41:30.800
[Amit Varma]: each other, because the first principles are different. Because libertarians value freedom,

00:41:30.800 --> 00:41:35.360
[Amit Varma]: left liberals value equality, conservatives value tradition, and they talk past each other all the

00:41:35.360 --> 00:41:39.200
[Amit Varma]: time, they can never talk to each other. And once you're cognizant of these different first

00:41:39.200 --> 00:41:43.280
[Amit Varma]: principles, maybe you can begin a dialogue. Are there other first principles that will suddenly

00:41:43.280 --> 00:41:47.840
[Amit Varma]: emerge? I don't know. And I can't imagine what they are. But that could easily be a lack of

00:41:47.840 --> 00:41:54.080
[Amit Varma]: imagination on my part. Like I said, it's an unknown unknown. But I see these as three ways of

00:41:54.080 --> 00:41:58.480
[Amit Varma]: three broad frameworks of looking at the world. And I know which my framework is. And I can talk

00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:04.880
[Amit Varma]: about that. And I think I can also, I can also, you know, have conversations with left liberals

00:42:04.880 --> 00:42:09.440
[Amit Varma]: and conservatives where I'm not talking past them, where I can engage with them on the basis of what

00:42:09.440 --> 00:42:13.440
[Amit Varma]: I understand of where they are coming from. But if you're asking, will there be some other way

00:42:13.440 --> 00:42:20.160
[Unknown]: of thinking that is beyond this? Who knows? So just wanted to ask one more thing in terms of,

00:42:20.160 --> 00:42:26.080
[Unknown]: you know, the guests on your show. And so have you ever thought of actually getting politicians,

