[Amit Varma]: the internet episode with Nikhil Pawar? It was very lively. We were arguing all the time. Vivek

01:08:50.560 --> 01:08:54.320
[Amit Varma]: Kaul is a frequent guest on the show. And we disagree over a lot of things. I mean, he's not

01:08:54.320 --> 01:08:58.800
[Amit Varma]: a libertarian, certainly like me, very close friend, very fine mind. So I try to engage with

01:08:58.800 --> 01:09:05.760
[Amit Varma]: people who don't think the way I do. At the same time, I must say that this quest for balance in

01:09:05.760 --> 01:09:10.480
[Amit Varma]: the personal domain, like this is a personal podcast, it's my podcast after all, is not

01:09:10.480 --> 01:09:16.080
[Amit Varma]: always necessary. For example, there are ideologies that I find repulsive, right? I will never bring

01:09:16.080 --> 01:09:21.360
[Amit Varma]: in, say, a Hindutva bigot here who will argue that Muslims don't belong in India. I find that

01:09:21.360 --> 01:09:25.520
[Amit Varma]: kind of thinking so repulsive, I will never have him here. Equally, I will never bring in somebody

01:09:25.520 --> 01:09:31.680
[Amit Varma]: here who, for example, doesn't care about individual rights or who believes in mass scale

01:09:31.680 --> 01:09:35.920
[Amit Varma]: coercion or social engineering. Again, I find that equally repulsive. Why should I engage with

01:09:35.920 --> 01:09:39.920
[Unknown]: those people? Those ideas are dangerous. Do you not subscribe to the idea that if you get someone

01:09:39.920 --> 01:09:45.280
[Unknown]: like that, you and him or her will find a common ground somewhere and they each of you go back

01:09:45.280 --> 01:09:49.840
[Amit Varma]: with something? Sure, no, I'd love to find common ground with conservatives and left liberals. But

01:09:49.840 --> 01:09:53.760
[Amit Varma]: I'm saying there are some categories of people on the far right and the far left, right, there is

01:09:53.760 --> 01:09:59.120
[Amit Varma]: no common ground possible with. So why even try if someone is going to sit across me and tell me

01:09:59.120 --> 01:10:03.520
[Amit Varma]: that Muslims don't belong in India, and it's a Hindu nation. I don't even want to have that

01:10:03.520 --> 01:10:09.600
[Amit Varma]: conversation. And maybe it's wrong on my part to react so strongly against that. But I don't want

01:10:09.600 --> 01:10:15.040
[Unknown]: to have that conversation. Okay. Vimal Roy on Facebook asked what's closer to you cricket or

